left_text: Epistomal suture forming obtuse paraocular lobe; dorsal gonostylus with long, narrow, hairless basal process extending mesad to midline
right_text: Epistomal suture forming right-angular paraocular lobe; dorsal gonostylus without such a mesal process

left_text: S4 broadly emarginate posteriorly, laterally bearing long, modiﬁed setae that are usually hidden; body length about 5 mm; inner lobe of ventral gonostylus without row of coarse setae
right_text: S4 not broadly emarginate, without long lateral setae; body length usually over 5 mm; inner lobe of ventral gonostylus bearing marginal row of coarse, ﬂattened setae (Fig. 67-10f)
